</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="23C03FF8D63EA00A6C8EB6222420A972" pageId="24" pageNumber="119" type="host plants">
<paragraph id="179E923153E8DE038B4A66BA12130543" pageId="24" pageNumber="119">Host plants.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BE3672A275051D10FA59F033EC10F083" pageId="24" pageNumber="119">
An old record by 
<bibRefCitation id="8818AB8CC5583DAC66AC23687D3A6214" author="Schwarz, EA" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington" pageId="52" pageNumber="147" pagination="231 - 233" refId="B172" refString="Schwarz, EA, 1890. Food-plants and food-habits of some North American Coleoptera. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington 1: 231 - 233" title="Food-plants and food-habits of some North American Coleoptera." volume="1" year="1890">Schwarz (1890)</bibRefCitation>
concerned 
<taxonomicName id="B79D2C688EDD9DF4E9D9DD7594215025" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Anacardiaceae" genus="Toxicodendron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Sapindales" pageId="24" pageNumber="119" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="radicans">
<emphasis id="3E817B0BA916DB1C72F6B515E5E1CEF3" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="119">Toxicodendron radicans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) Kuntze) (
<taxonomicName id="866C9667EA35C8B5C42F8AD835778EA2" genus="Anachardiaceae" lsidName="" pageId="24" pageNumber="119" rank="genus">Anachardiaceae</taxonomicName>
), but this was probably based on misidentified specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="863E4082539015D630ADBA0F812D8B95" baseAuthorityName="F. E. Melsheimer" baseAuthorityYear="1847" class="Hexapoda" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Pachybrachis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tridens">
<emphasis id="CD4A7F8763E4CF976771EF006096FDFA" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="119">Pachybrachis tridens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="088BFCA1C47D1C28D87B094A6174EDEB" author="Clark, SM" journalOrPublisher="Occasional Publications of the West Virginia Department of Agriculture" pageId="45" pageNumber="140" refId="B44" refString="Clark, SM, LeDoux, DG, Seeno, TN, Riley, EG, Gilbert, AJ, Sullivan, JM, 2004. Host plants of leaf beetle species occurring in the United States and Canada. In: The Coleopterists Society, Special Publication No. 2., 476 pp." title="Host plants of leaf beetle species occurring in the United States and Canada." volumeTitle="The Coleopterists Society, Special Publication No. 2." year="2004">Clark et al. (2004)</bibRefCitation>
reviewed the literature. More recently, Webster swept it from 
<taxonomicName id="88259848C17255D126155C928000CB60" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Comptonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Valvatida" pageId="24" pageNumber="119" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="peregrina">
<emphasis id="4F276EA5FD5C85267CDFEB0C87AF2C10" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="119">Comptonia peregrina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="C11F99B947A0C1866BAAD197152D4E40" genus="Myricaceae" lsidName="" pageId="24" pageNumber="119" rank="genus">Myricaceae</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="1939957E31FFA1F17764A8DE6D3A5428" author="Webster, RP" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="52" pageNumber="147" pagination="321 - 348" refId="B181" refString="Webster, RP, LeSage, L, DeMerchant, I, 2012. New Coleoptera records from New Brunswick, Canada: Megalopodidae and Chrysomelidae. ZooKeys 179: 321 - 348" title="New Coleoptera records from New Brunswick, Canada: Megalopodidae and Chrysomelidae." volume="179" year="2012">Webster et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
). Recent surveying in Kentucky barrens/prairies by 
<bibRefCitation id="BD4FCC9BA72174F603DB6C15F8FDB87E" author="Barney, RJ" journalOrPublisher="The Coleopterists Bulletin" pageId="43" pageNumber="138" pagination="15 - 19" publicationUrl="10.1649/0010-065X-65.1.15" refId="B11" refString="Barney, RJ, Hall, SL, 2011. New host plant records for selected Cryptocephaline leaf beetles (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae) in Kentucky. The Coleopterists Bulletin 65 (1): 15 - 19, 10.1649/0010-065X-65.1.15" title="New host plant records for selected Cryptocephaline leaf beetles (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae) in Kentucky." url="10.1649/0010-065X-65.1.15" volume="65" year="2011">Barney et al. (2011)</bibRefCitation>
cited 
<taxonomicName id="06032B9BC5731DCE575C9B21DC9C5920" baseAuthorityName="F. E. Melsheimer" baseAuthorityYear="1847" class="Hexapoda" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Pachybrachis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="m-nigrum">
<emphasis id="17520E030C315B851CC65CC3280B82E6" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="119">Pachybrachis m-nigrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected from and found to feed on St. 
<normalizedToken id="62B0257B12EAB63598519911A6287B5A" originalValue="John’s-wort">John's-wort</normalizedToken>
, 
<taxonomicName id="3519AA3D052ADF41C534169A1D0F62E2" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Clusiaceae" genus="Hypericum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Guttiferales" pageId="24" pageNumber="119" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="dolabriforme">
<emphasis id="A6766656D0EBAA69F14E2712AD56678A" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="119">Hypericum dolabriforme</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Vent. (
<taxonomicName id="D03202673C86AC6F4B7FA08812F35AE6" genus="Clusiaceae" lsidName="" pageId="24" pageNumber="119" rank="genus">Clusiaceae</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="71F6E426BB35CA46EF3E052E07B092E2" author="Barney, RJ" journalOrPublisher="The Coleopterists Bulletin" pageId="43" pageNumber="138" pagination="15 - 19" publicationUrl="10.1649/0010-065X-65.1.15" refId="B11" refString="Barney, RJ, Hall, SL, 2011. New host plant records for selected Cryptocephaline leaf beetles (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae) in Kentucky. The Coleopterists Bulletin 65 (1): 15 - 19, 10.1649/0010-065X-65.1.15" title="New host plant records for selected Cryptocephaline leaf beetles (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae) in Kentucky." url="10.1649/0010-065X-65.1.15" volume="65" year="2011">Barney and Hall (2011)</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4CBED003AD214D47D64BF2698E867A54" pageId="24" pageNumber="119" type="comments">
<paragraph id="D0014E3CAE5A5BC1DCB1BB481B5A2D2F" pageId="24" pageNumber="119">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="010C7BEBEF8B2A3BEB5B9F10293F986C" pageId="24" pageNumber="119">
Based upon external morphlogy, these specimens appear to be 
<taxonomicName id="7AEF66A963D91EC14794D177217F0FD8" baseAuthorityName="F. E. Melsheimer" baseAuthorityYear="1847" class="Hexapoda" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Pachybrachis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="m-nigrum">
<emphasis id="7E9F34FDADD32D10026466802EF97CEC" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="119">Pachybrachis m-nigrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, extensive dissections of material from across the eastern half of the US reveal an externally similar species, but with a distinctly different aedeagus, from the midwestern states (Barney, unpublished data).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
